== Chermoula ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(minced), 2 tbsp @olive oil{},
a pinch of @garlic{pinch}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{to taste}. Add @lemon{1}(zested and juiced) juice to taste and as much @jalapeño{1}(minced, removing ribs and seeds for less heat) as you like. Taste and add more garlic if desired.

== Lemon Cream ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, @salt{pinch}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Basmati Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add ¼ of the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced); cook, stirring,
until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, one of the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Tagine ==

While rice cooks, heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @zucchini{1}(trimmed, halved lengthwise, and cut into 1/2-inch-thick
half-moons) and remaining onion. Cook, stirring, until softened and lightly
browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon}, remaining @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and
minced), and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add 1/3 cup water and remaining @veggie stock concentrate{1} to pan.

Stir in @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}(drained and rinsed) and bring tagine to a low simmer. Cook until liquid has slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low; stir in 1 tbsp @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between plates and top with tagine, @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce}, and @dried apricots{1%ounce}. Drizzle with lemon crema and chermoula. Drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired. Cut any remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side.

> Toast almonds before adding if you like.